Description: An R toolkit for spatial-omics analysis that quantifies multi-scale
    spatial structure and gene co-occurrence across tissue grids. It supports
    flexible binning, graph-based modeling, and module discovery to interpret
    microenvironment organization from high-resolution platforms. For Xenium
    ingest, an optional Python plus pyarrow fallback is supported when some
    transcript parquet layouts are not queryable through R arrow alone.
